<paragraph id="2D65AC03D07FAF663C9D33879328302C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7BFD365BF3A32F4CE406EF6EBCDEBC3E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Iran, Tehran Province, river in the Darban-Tal (Darban Valley), 2100 m a.s.l.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8F22A27916F771363AC3FD19499C11A8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2EA8D7224BEC8E51903DA65425FD7A64" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="974244FA9F527C994C789F0F548299F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Northern Iran. Species endemic to the Alborz Mountains (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F31C92112F840CA63EE05772DFA5F08A" captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. Geographical (left) and vertical (right) distribution of Epeorus (Caucasiron) iranicus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471943" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="49C5743572557D6C6C8698C69B1EF78D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="B8BB85E9B9426CEFB249CDA6CB24D3E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DE3AB52D74E4122CEB8F1D551EB2D444" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Larvae inhabit streams at altitudes above 2000 m a.s.l. in the western and central Alborz. Altitudinal range of sampling sites 2020-2440 m a.s.l. (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4005E68332B539A1F28FF13F480611F7" captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. Geographical (left) and vertical (right) distribution of Epeorus (Caucasiron) iranicus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471943" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">21</figureCitation>
). Often syntopic with 
<taxonomicName id="205789DCD2917340BB5492E9E4EB954C" genus="E." lsidName="E. (C.) alborzicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="alborzicus" subGenus="C.">E. (C.) alborzicus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="01654C8A7C87A0CC6C3326375AB426E7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="main morphological diagnostics of larvae">
<paragraph id="96A7EE062E954BD29B8FC07CD3BB3905" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Main morphological diagnostics of larvae.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1F67C45220DB244FBD6E1F48D99F283B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(i) abdominal sterna II-VI with a pair of oblique stripes; nerve ganglia often with stripes or spots (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="85F84B5A608A1AD2EB4547101272A537" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Epeorus (Caucasiron) iranicus, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F middle leg in dorsal view G, H abdominal terga (arrows point antero-lateral stripes of medial macula) I, J abdominal sterna II-VI K gills VII (in natural position from ventral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471944" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22B, I, J</figureCitation>
); (ii) abdominal terga V-VII with stripe-like medial macula and a pair of distinct antero-lateral stripes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AF364E4F3BB81057CCDEE7434CC1BBDE" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Epeorus (Caucasiron) iranicus, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F middle leg in dorsal view G, H abdominal terga (arrows point antero-lateral stripes of medial macula) I, J abdominal sterna II-VI K gills VII (in natural position from ventral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471944" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22G</figureCitation>
, arrows); (iii) femora with rounded medial hypodermal spot (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="64D664C4E1DE619E97004B8248CF128D" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Epeorus (Caucasiron) iranicus, larva: A habitus in dorsal view B habitus in ventral view C habitus in lateral view D head of male in dorsal view E head of female in dorsal view F middle leg in dorsal view G, H abdominal terga (arrows point antero-lateral stripes of medial macula) I, J abdominal sterna II-VI K gills VII (in natural position from ventral view)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471944" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22F</figureCitation>
); (iv) gill III with well-developed projection (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="283CBD1CFDA507E8528992F9985DCCCD" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Epeorus (Caucasiron) iranicus, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) J sternum IX of female K, L abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view (arrow points on postero-lateral projection)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471945" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">23G</figureCitation>
); (v) setae on abdominal terga hair-like (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2AB2C5A46E22179163EA2BCCBB51A7A5" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Epeorus (Caucasiron) iranicus, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) J sternum IX of female K, L abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view (arrow points on postero-lateral projection)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471945" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">23E</figureCitation>
); (vi) tergum X with poorly developed postero-lateral projections (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B017491527E53A4B973987FE65B5CED5" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Epeorus (Caucasiron) iranicus, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) J sternum IX of female K, L abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view (arrow points on postero-lateral projection)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471945" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">23K</figureCitation>
, arrow) or without postero-lateral projections (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F150BE533079FFE58946A03F29D5BBA1" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Epeorus (Caucasiron) iranicus, larva: A labrum (left half in dorsal view right half in ventral view) B incisors of left mandible C incisors of right mandible D setae on dorsal surface of femora E surface and posterior margin of abdominal tergum VII F gill I G gill III H gill VII (flattened on slide) I gill VII (in natural position from ventral view) J sternum IX of female K, L abdominal segments VIII-X in lateral view (arrow points on postero-lateral projection)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.986.56276.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/471945" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">23L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2C0CDEA6994085E9226B2081977726F8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="EDBA10CB58BA0377FC0209513F79BA1D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CFB5DA8CE3B63C30F5BC284AF14CB224" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="CAF955C571EFBA14F441091AF61C1BE6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="01FF990AEC11F397BED6E7FB0390A73B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Morphology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Coloration pattern on abdominal sterna as in 
<taxonomicName id="5F891F469B3A306935F0BD8D1E855199" genus="E." lsidName="E. (C.) caucasicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caucasicus" subGenus="C.">E. (C.) caucasicus</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
